---
// DAY-166 / DAY-206. The single conversion CTA.
//
// The href points at GitHub's
// `/releases/latest/download/Dayseam.dmg` redirect: a stable,
// version-agnostic URL that 302s to whatever the most recent
// release's `Dayseam.dmg` asset is. The release workflow at
// `dayseam/dayseam` (`.github/workflows/release.yml`, DAY-206)
// uploads `Dayseam.dmg` as an alias next to the versioned
// `Dayseam-v${VERSION}.dmg` on every release, so this URL never
// goes stale. The browser reads `Content-Disposition: attachment`
// off the redirected response and starts the download immediately
// — the user no longer has to land on the GitHub release page and
// hunt for the right asset, which was the previous behaviour and
// the single biggest friction point in the install flow.
//
// We avoid:
//   - hardcoding `Dayseam-v${VERSION}.dmg` (404s the moment a new
//     release publishes — GitHub's redirect needs a byte-exact
//     filename, no globs);
//   - resolving the asset URL client-side via `api.github.com`
//     (adds JS to a static Astro page and hits the
//     60-req/hr-per-IP unauthenticated rate limit on shared
//     corporate NAT egresses).
//
// The "View source on GitHub" link below stays unchanged — users
// who want the changelog or want to inspect the binary still have
// a one-click path to the repo from this section. Anyone landing
// here from the keyboard with download-blocked browsers can also
// follow that link to the release page manually.
---

<section
  id="download"
  class="border-y border-white/5 bg-gradient-to-b from-charcoal-900/80 to-charcoal-800/80 py-24"
  aria-label="Download Dayseam"
>
  <div class="mx-auto max-w-3xl px-6 text-center">
    <h2 class="text-balance text-3xl font-semibold text-zinc-50 sm:text-4xl">
      Ready in about a minute
    </h2>
    <p class="mt-4 text-balance text-zinc-400">
      Signed and notarized macOS build. Apple Silicon or Intel, same DMG.
      No installer account, no uninstaller to hunt down later
    </p>

    <div class="mt-10 flex flex-col items-center justify-center gap-4 sm:flex-row">
      <a
        href="https://github.com/dayseam/dayseam/releases/latest/download/Dayseam.dmg"
        class="inline-flex items-center gap-2 rounded-lg bg-cream px-6 py-3 text-sm font-semibold text-charcoal-900 transition-transform hover:scale-[1.02] focus-visible:scale-[1.02]"
        rel="noopener noreferrer"
      >
        Download for macOS
        <svg viewBox="0 0 24 24" width="16" height="16" fill="currentColor" aria-hidden="true">
          <path
            d="M12 3v12m0 0 5-5m-5 5-5-5M5 21h14"
            stroke="currentColor"
            stroke-width="2"
            stroke-linecap="round"
            stroke-linejoin="round"
            fill="none"
          />
        </svg>
      </a>
      <a
        href="https://github.com/dayseam/dayseam"
        class="inline-flex items-center gap-2 rounded-lg border border-white/10 px-6 py-3 text-sm font-medium text-zinc-100 transition-colors hover:bg-white/5 focus-visible:bg-white/5"
        target="_blank"
        rel="noopener noreferrer"
      >
        View source on GitHub
      </a>
    </div>

    <p class="mt-6 text-xs text-zinc-500">
      Windows and Linux builds are on the post v1.0 roadmap.
      <a
        href="https://github.com/dayseam/dayseam/issues?q=is%3Aissue+label%3Aplatform"
        class="underline hover:text-zinc-300 focus-visible:text-zinc-300"
        target="_blank"
        rel="noopener noreferrer"
      >
        Track platform issues on GitHub
      </a>
    </p>
  </div>
</section>
